{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"09d5ffa9-c33d-4011-86f6-d96c029574a3","content":"Found **1 untestable static call** in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n| File | Line | Call |\n|------|------|------|\n| `views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` |\n\n**Why it's a problem:** Direct calls to `datetime.now()` can't be easily controlled in tests, making time-dependent logic hard to verify.\n\n**Recommended fix:** Use Django's `django.utils.timezone.now()` (which `freezegun` or `time_machine` can mock), or inject the clock as a dependency:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis allows you to use `freezegun.freeze_time` or `time_machine.travel` in tests to control the returned time. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a4cb148-ad49-480e-b40d-3be11ad6e0b7","outputTokens":217,"requestId":"981A:23633C:1313469:17FBD7E:69FFF414"},"id":"e0d41d68-3f13-43f8-86a2-6ee756e4bf80","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:57:30.358Z","parentId":"da6c90ba-abfd-4a0d-8734-ab9cba0101f7"}
